COVID 19 raport¶

Poniej widoczna jest tabela, zaimportowana z profilu CSSEGISandData na platformie GitHub. Tabela zawiera dane dotyczce zachorowa i zgonw na COVID 19. Zawiera dane od 21 stycznia 2020, do chwili obecnej, aktualizowana jest raz dziennie.

import copy
import matplotlib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

tmp = MultipleData.filter(regex='\d{1,2}\/\d{1,2}\/\d{4}', axis=1).filter(regex='^0$', axis=0).rename({0: 'cases'}, axis=0)

dates = tmp.columns

tmp = tmp.astype(float)

list1 = tmp.values.tolist()
list2 = copy.deepcopy(list1)

length = len(list1[0])

for day in range(length):
    if day != 0:
        list1[0][day]= list2[0][day] / list2[0][day-1]

list1[0][0]=0

fig = plt.plot(dates,list1[0])
fig = matplotlib.pyplot.gcf()
fig.set_size_inches(21.5, 10.5)
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
fig.savefig('growth.png', dpi=100)

ConfirmedGer = ConfirmedGer.set_index('Country/Region', drop=True).filter(regex='\d{1,2}\/\d{1,2}\/\d{2}', axis=1)
LatestConfirmedGermany = ConfirmedGer.iloc[:,-1].Germany
DeathsGermany = Deaths_raw[Deaths_raw['Country/Region']=='Germany']
DeathsGermany = DeathsGermany.set_index('Country/Region', drop=True).filter(regex='\d{1,2}\/\d{1,2}\/\d{2}', axis=1)
LatestDeathGermany = DeathsGermany.iloc[:,-1].Germany
RecoveriesGermany = Recoveries_raw[Recoveries_raw['Country/Region']=='Germany']
RecoveriesGermany = RecoveriesGermany.set_index('Country/Region', drop=True).filter(regex='\d{1,2}\/\d{1,2}\/\d{2}', axis=1)
LatestRecoveriesGermany = RecoveriesGermany.iloc[:,-1].Germany
LatestConfirmedGermany = LatestConfirmedGermany - LatestDeathGermany - LatestRecoveriesGermany

###################################################################################################

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 3), subplot_kw=dict(aspect="equal"))

recipe = [str(LatestConfirmedGermany) + " currently sick",
          str(LatestDeathGermany) + " deaths",
          str(LatestRecoveriesGermany) + " recovered"]

data = [LatestConfirmedGermany, LatestDeathGermany, LatestRecoveriesGermany]

wedges, texts = ax.pie(data, wedgeprops=dict(width=0.5), startangle=-90)

bbox_props = dict(boxstyle="square,pad=0.3", fc="w", ec="k", lw=0.72)
kw = dict(arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="-"),
          bbox=bbox_props, zorder=0, va="center")

for i, p in enumerate(wedges):
    ang = (p.theta2 - p.theta1)/2. + p.theta1
    y = np.sin(np.deg2rad(ang))
    x = np.cos(np.deg2rad(ang))
    horizontalalignment = {-1: "right", 1: "left"}[int(np.sign(x))]
    connectionstyle = "angle,angleA=0,angleB={}".format(ang)
    kw["arrowprops"].update({"connectionstyle": connectionstyle})
    ax.annotate(recipe[i], xy=(x, y), xytext=(1.35*np.sign(x), 1.4*y),
                horizontalalignment=horizontalalignment, **kw)

ax.set_title("Germany")

###################################################################################################
